709236f-a.text:
(1
Fifth Ave., West side, between West 142nd and 143rd Streets. The 369th Regiment Infantry Armory, on the west side of Fifth Ave., between West 142nd and 143rd Streets, as seen from the Harlem River. This
was the proposed site of the 15th Regiment Armory.
November 29, 1936.
P. L. Sperr.
The same at an earlier date . Also shown is a view westward on
West 142nd Street.
September 16, 1935.
P. L. Sperr.
